Avoid Common Mortgage Mistakes
Many buyers unintentionally delay approval by making avoidable financial decisions during the mortgage process.
Avoid:
    • Changing jobs before closing 
    • Opening new credit accounts 
    • Making large purchases 
    • Missing bill payments 
    • Depositing unexplained large sums into bank accounts 
Maintaining financial stability until your loan closes helps prevent unexpected complications.
